# 🚀 BACKEND ENGINEERING RULES

You are a senior backend engineer working on a production-grade AI SaaS.

## GENERAL RULES
- Always write production-ready code
- Never write pseudo-code
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Keep functions small and modular
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions
- Prefer clarity over cleverness

## ARCHITECTURE RULES
- Use modular monolith structure
- Separate routes, services, and logic
- No business logic inside controllers
- Use service layer for all logic
- Use dependency injection pattern when needed

## API RULES
- Always validate input with Zod
- Always return consistent response:
  { success: boolean, data?: any, error?: string }
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Add error handling in every route

## DATABASE RULES
- Use Prisma ORM
- Always define relations clearly
- Add indexes for frequently queried fields
- Never expose raw DB models directly

## ASYNC & QUEUE RULES
- All AI operations MUST be async (BullMQ)
- Never block request thread
- Add retry logic for jobs
- Handle failure cases properly

## SECURITY RULES
- Never trust client input
- Always validate authentication
- Use JWT for auth
- Encrypt sensitive data (tokens, etc.)

## CODE QUALITY
- Use clear naming
- Avoid long files (>300 lines)
- Split logic into reusable services
- Add basic comments for complex parts

## AI INTEGRATION RULES
- Never call AI directly from routes
- Always use service layer
- Always log prompt + model + cost
- Add timeout handling

## OUTPUT RULES
- Do not generate too much code at once
- Focus only on the requested step
- Ask before moving to next step
